explicit

Interface MDPGeneric<Value>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Model, NondetModel
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    CTMDP, MDP
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CTMDPSimple, MDPAdditionalChoices, MDPDroppedAllChoices, MDPDroppedChoicesCached, MDPEquiv, MDPExplicit, MDPFromDTMC, MDPSimple, MDPSparse, MDPView, ParamModel, STPGExplicit

    public interface MDPGeneric<Value>
extends NondetModel
    Interface for classes that provide (read) access to an explicit-state MDP, gathering the generic methods, i.e., those that are independent of the underlying value type used for the transition probabilities.
    This allows use of these methods e.g. in the explicit and parametric engines.

        default void prob0step(java.util.BitSet subset,
                       java.util.BitSet u,
                       boolean forall,
                       java.util.BitSet result)
        Perform a single step of precomputation algorithm Prob0, i.e., for states i in subset, set bit i of result iff, for all/some choices, there is a transition to a state in u. Quantification over choices is determined by forall.
        Parameters:
        subset - Only compute for these states
        u - Set of states u
        forall - For-all or there-exists (true=for-all, false=there-exists)
        result - Store results here
